Yes, CSS can be used to enhance the look and feel of a mortgage calculator built with HTML and JavaScript. CSS can be used to style the layout, font, color, and other visual aspects of the calculator. Here's an example of how to use CSS to style a basic mortgage calculator built with HTML and JavaScript:
```php
<html>
  <head>
    <style>
      .calculator {
        width: 500px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        text-align: center;
        font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      }
      .calculator h1 {
        font-size: 36px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      .calculator input[type="text"] {
        font-size: 24px;
        padding: 10px;
        width: 100%;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }
      .calculator button {
        padding: 10px 20px;
        font-size: 24px;
        background-color: #4CAF50;
        color: white;
        border: none;
        cursor: pointer;
      }
      .calculator .result {
        font-size: 36px;
        color: #4CAF50;
        margin-top: 20px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="calculator">
      <h1>Mortgage Calculator</h1>
      <input type="text" id="principal" placeholder="Principal">
      <input type="text" id="interest" placeholder="Interest Rate">
      <input type="text" id="years" placeholder="Loan Term (years)">
      <button id="calculate">Calculate</button>
      <div class="result" id="result"></div>
    </div>
    <script>
      var calculateButton = document.getElementById("calculate");
      calculateButton.addEventListener("click", function() {
        var principal = document.getElementById("principal").value;
        var interest = document.getElementById("interest").value / 100 / 12;
        var years = document.getElementById("years").value * 12;
        var result = document.getElementById("result");
        var payment = principal * interest / (1 - (Math.pow(1/(1 + interest), years)));
        result.innerHTML = "$" + payment.toFixed(2) + " is your payment.";
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
```
This example uses CSS to style the calculator layout, including the width, margin, text alignment, font, and color. The inputs for the principal amount, interest rate, and loan term are styled with CSS to have a font size of 24px, padding of 10px, and a width of 100%. The calculate button is also styled with CSS to have a padding of 10px, font size of 24px, and a green background color. The result is styled to have a font size of 36px and a green color.
